basics.name: Harrison Law
basics.label: Student
basics.summary: I am studying for a B.S. in Computer Science in the Department of Information and Computer Sciences at the University of Hawaii. I expect to graduate in Fall, 2026.

highlights: Assist customers with various needs and questions regarding product information
Handle financial transactions and process customer product returns
Created programs to analyze and graph the density of strands in a particle respirator using MATLAB to determine the effectiveness of prototype air filters
Conducted research on the impact of certain environmental factors on certain bodily functions using various sensors and presented findings
Analyzed data generated from research using MATLAB into graphs to determine the most relevant factors in creating a personalized heat index
Engineered programs to analyze and interpret data from geospatial images to assess their terrain properties
Operated motion capture cameras to track the position of a rover moving across various terrain and used the accompanying software to record and render data from the cameras
Collaborated with other interns to install and integrate software in multiple depth and motion sensing robotics cameras
Solved and analyzed various problems involving different data structures and algorithms
